Summary: Star traveling south to north at 6:04 horizon to horizon/ west of orion in morning sky
divs: Sighting DetailsFed Ex planes usualy buzz the house early morning. I was listening to st johns church bells rang at 6"00 am I was looking at orion in the early sky when I saw a solid star traveling probably 12-20 thousand miles an hour. Altitude was 80-120 thousand ft. Probably space station . star was very bright reflective of the sun in the horizon. Should appear tonight if it is a satellite tracking that course. I live on a golf course so the stars are quite bright with low ground light . I notices a two star object 30 days ago . had to be humongous . same altitude but distance between stars either made it huge or two objects on perfect path linear.no variance.I am sure this was a large satellite ..seemed to be traveling in orbital state.
